          "opus_side": null,
          "thesis": "**Operating margin resilience and cash generation durability.** Despite a flat full-year net profit growth of 0.36% YoY in FY26 (Mar 2026: 13,266 Cr vs Mar 2025: 13,218 Cr), Wipro has expanded operating margins from 20.2% in Mar 2025 to 19.2% in Mar 2026 (per Screener), and delivered 17.6% operating margin in Q3 FY26 at the high end of the 17-17.5% guided band. This is achieved despite HARMAN DTS integration (which management said would be 'margin-dilutive') and restructuring charges of INR 263 Cr in Q3. **Operating cash flow remained robust at 135% of net income in Q3 and 127.7% for full year FY26** (16,943 Cr OCF vs 13,266 Cr net profit), enabling the company to distribute >$1.3B in dividends (INR 11 per share equivalent) in FY26 while maintaining a gross cash position of $6.5B. This demonstrates **operational discipline and financial stability** even amid demand headwinds. The company is not sacrificing profitability or financial flexibility to chase revenue growth\u2014a disciplined stance that protects shareholder interests."
